Hi! Man I never knew before how much I HATE babysitting!!!! I had to babysit for my church on Saturday.  Me and my brother and another girl were all going to babysit the kids of the people who were going to the Christmas dinner.  We figured that there would be about 10 kids and that it would not be to bad and we were getting paid $20 each.  Well I'll tell you- it was not worth $20.  Instead of 10 kids there were 20 and we had to watch them for 4 hours and there were no toys for them to play with! The only thing there was a TV with movies that they did not want to watch and some stuffed animals.  Usually in a group of kids there is like 1 or 2 trouble kids and when you get them to calm down then everyone else is ok too, well not thind time- oh no! There were 7 trouble kids! One I eventually got to settle down after he was kicking me and kicked my knee out of place.  The other 6 were just trouble the entire time and this 1 girl wanted to be held the entire night so I was holding her then her brother wanted to be held so I was holding both of them and one was complaining and wining in my ear then this one kid had an issue with sound and I had to keep taking him out of the room to a quiet place because he was going nuts with every sound and they were throwing the stuffed animals so we had to take those away and we had to take the tables out of the room because they were climing on them and wouldnt get down, then they were running around with the chairs and kept running out of the room because they all wanted water like every 5 seconds.  And thats not even all of it but I really don't want to remember anything else from it.  That night I actually dreampt about them and woke up at 3 in hte morning because of it.  I will never babaysit again!  Anyway on to the better things that have been going on, I have an 86 in Physc, though I'm not doing the best in my other classes, I'll have to bring those up.  I'm really annoyed because I got up early today to go to school to make up a quiz for Mr. Flamm, but when I got there, he was not there.  I got to spend half an hour running around the school looking for him and I couldnt find him anywhere, he told my teacher that he was in the social studies office but I looked there and he wasnt so I'm a little ticked at him and they decided to cut ASL out of the Christmas assembly- which really sucks and we are all mad because of it and we are going to try to get chorus or band or someone to cut out one of their songs so that we can perform.  So ya all of that stuff sucks but Wes is keeping me from getting to angry and hitting my head against the wall because all that stuff is really stupid.  Anyway ok I really think that I have written enough, especially since almost all of my friends have heard all of it already. BYE!

QUESTION OF THE DAY: Can you "zone out" and be "in the zone" at the same time?

Wow I havnt updated this thing in forever, actually I'm surprised that my name is still on here.  Life is fun.  I hate all my classes and school in general for that matter but everything else rocks.  I have been running around everywhere trying to get my moms Christmas present together and everyone elses presents too.  I got to do the craft fair today and that was a lot of fun.  I was there with the ASL club and we were running the face painting booth and all these adorable little kids came to get their face painted.  I got a pretty Pointsetta painted on my cheek and I got to paint a snowman on Diana (only because I bought a shinny rose tattoo) and I got to paint a snowflake on Wes (he was so sweet, he came to see me and brought me 3 white roses just for teh hell of it and let me paint his face and stayed to watch me sign Christmas songs).  Then tonight my brother and me are going to my church to babysit while the Christmas dinner is going on and we get paid 20 bucks each to do it which is cool.  I can't wait until Christmas but I really am not ready yet because I need a lot of time to get everyones presents together.  All the snow is awsome!  I don't think I have aver been so happy to have snow before.  Although the bad thing that's going on lately is that I have to go to the hospital soon to get my knee checked out because it never healed and I have been trying to go for the longest time and havnt been able to so I'm supposed to go this upcoming week but I'll probably end up putting it off again, oh well I'll get it done eventually.  I have to get an MRI and all of that so I'm really in no rush to go.  Oh well, thats really all I have to say for now- LATER!!!

Hopefully I will be able to get in touch with all of my friends again and be even happier. I send smiles to everyone and I hope they are as happy as I am right now. Now I am going to go sleep until I go out anywhere today (I havn't had any insomnia in so long and I'm loving it!) bye!!
